        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-14 17:40:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: Looks good to me, approved\n\nIt isn't clear why this patch was resubmitted, rather than just restarting the testing?  It is less work to restart the test (by reporting the Hudson build number to be retested to one of the testers: Sarah, Li Wei, Minh, Yu Jian, Chris), or by logging into build.whamcloud.com and restarting the build.  That avoids the need to re-inspect the patch, and in the case of just restarting testing on the same build it also avoids the need to rebuild the patch.\n\nIf you are resubmitting patches to master for any reason, please begin to use tabs for indentation in the entire patch.  This is especially important for the OFD patches and others landing from orion, since they are making large changes to the OST stack and have the chance to convert large parts of this code to use tabs without the need for useless tab-only patches.\n\nIt also makes sense to begin using tabs for indentation in orion, but this can be done on a patch-by-patch basis so that it doesn't disrupt all of the ongoing work.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
